🔧 CREATE Command in SQL
The CREATE command is used to create database objects such as:

. Databases
. Tables
. Views
. Procedures
. Functions
. Triggers

📌 Creating a Database
-- Create a database
CREATE DATABASE COLLEGE;

-- Show all databases
SHOW DATABASES;

-- Delete (drop) a database
DROP DATABASE COLLEGE;

-- Show databases again
SHOW DATABASES;

📘 What is a Table?
. A table is a collection of rows and columns.
. A table is also called a relation in relational databases.
. A column is also known as a field or attribute.
. A row is also known as a tuple or record.
. The complete table structure + data is known as an instance.

🏗️ How to Create a Table
Syntax:
CREATE TABLE table_name (
    column1 datatype(size),
    column2 datatype(size),
    ...,
    columnN datatype(size)
);

🧠 Example Question:
Q: Write a query to create a table named stud_info with 5 columns: roll, name, course, mark, and gender.

Answer:
CREATE TABLE stud_info (
    Roll INT,
    Name VARCHAR(30),
    Course VARCHAR(20),
    Mark INT,
    Gender CHAR
);

🧪 Practical Example
-- Create the database
CREATE DATABASE COLLEGE;

-- Select the database for use
USE COLLEGE;

-- Create the table
CREATE TABLE stud_info (
    Roll INT,
    Name VARCHAR(30),
    Course VARCHAR(20),
    Mark INT,
    Gender CHAR
);

-- Show all databases
SHOW DATABASES;

-- View the contents of the table
SELECT * FROM stud_info;



